From 5e07dcc9c598693068fd1b62d1954a04eff7843f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Cursor Agent <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 19:31:24 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(psl): thread extension pack refs for index-type
 validation

Wire composedExtensionPackRefs through the standard PSL authoring path:

- @prisma-next/postgres defineConfig passes extension descriptors to
  prismaContract so indexTypes registered on packs are available at config time
- CLI contract emit passes stack.extensionPacks as composedExtensionPackRefs
  in ContractSourceContext at runtime
- PSL provider prefers context refs, falling back to static config options
- ContractSourceContext gains optional composedExtensionPackRefs

Fixes PSL @@index(..., type: "bm25"|"gist"|...) rejecting registered
extension index types with "unregistered index type" when using the normal
defineConfig / contract emit path. TS lane was unaffected.

Closes prisma/prisma-next#895
